gomodel:SYNGO_5449  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: KIF3B binds to the NR2A complex.\n\nFigure 2: KIF3B is essential for the postsynaptic localization of NR2A and NR2B in hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 3: KIF3B transports NR2A, but not NR2B.\n\nFigure 7: The expression of KIF3B, but not mutated KIF3B, restores spine morphology and NR2A surface expression.. Experimental description: Results: \"Immunoblotting of crude extracts of the Kif3b+/- mouse brains ...\"\n\nanti-KIF3B polyclonal antibody (1:500, Takeda et al, 2000) (PMID:10725338)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
